# Section 12 — Testing Strategy & Validation Matrix

---

# 12.1 Introduction

A successful deployment does not necessarily mean that an application is correct.

For an AI system composed of multiple interacting components, every subsystem must be validated individually before validating the complete workflow.

The Study Abroad Finder project therefore adopted a layered testing strategy.

Instead of testing the entire application immediately, each component was isolated and verified independently.

Only after every subsystem behaved correctly was the complete architecture validated.

This chapter documents the complete testing methodology.

---

# 12.2 Testing Philosophy

The project followed a simple principle.

```
Small Components

↓

Individual Validation

↓

Integration Validation

↓

End-to-End Validation
```

This significantly reduced debugging complexity and increased confidence in every stage.

